> From box to table in just 10 minutes, this recipe is the perfect vegetarian solution to busy evenings (or lunchtimes!). Paired with fresh tomatoes, mint, nutritious brown rice and quinoa, this recipe is as nourishing as it is delicious.

Cut the @halloumi{250%g} into roughly 1cm thick slices.

Halve the @cherry plum tomatoes{200} and pop them in a large #salad bowl{}.

Pick the @mint{1} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop, (discard the stalks).

Roughly chop the @wild rocket{40%g} leaves. Add half the chopped mint to the bowl with the tomatoes.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When hot, add the halloumi and fry until golden on both sides, turning occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{} stir together the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @honey{15%ml} and @olive oil{2%tbsp}.

Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}.

Cook the @brown rice & quinoa{1%portion} according to pack instructions.

Add the brown rice and quinoa, the rocket and half the @walnuts{20%g} to the bowl with the tomatoes and toss together.

Drizzle over half the dressing and toss again. Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

Serve the warm salad in bowls topped with the fried halloumi and a scattering of the remaining walnuts and mint.

Finish with a drizzle of the remaining dressing.